text:
The last few months have been tough on Roman.
 Clawing his way to one of the top journalists wasn't an easy ride but he didn't regret a single minute of it. In the end it was all woth it. Not only was his last entry a roaring success but his boss asked him to fil in for him at the gala.
 To say Roman was thrilled would be an understatemnt.
 Luck was finally on his side.

There was only one issue Roman had to solve before goin out for the evening. And that was his clothing choice.
 Call him shallow but according to Roman first impressions are very important. He became recognizable due to his clothing always being adored by something red. Be it the suit itself, a scarf or a hat. But the party throwers deceided to make the gala a sea themed party due to some important marine general being a guest of honour.
 That left Roman with the choice whether he should choose his usual getup and stand out or blend in with his more tonned down green suit.

After much delibaration the journalist finaly decided to wear the green suit. It's not his usual color but he has to admit it does bring out his eyes.
 As much as he likes to stand out maybe waring something in tune with the dress code will highten his chances of securing some interviews. Adjusting his tie Roman notices the time.
 'SH*T' he swears loudly trying to tie the tie faster but only managing it to tangle it.
 There is no way he's gonna make it on time, unless he's gonna take a shortcut through the notorious Crystal therithory where he'll mind end up with more holes in his body then swiss cheese.
 Then again he'd prefer to be punctual to his first important Gala.
 Is his life really worth risking making a good first impression?

Roman is only a few meters away from the party when hears somebody.
 'Hey punk!' As soon as Roman turns around a gun is pressed to his stomach.'You shouldn't have come here.'Roman gulps down, he really thought luck was on hisa side tonight. 'Any last word' Roman can already see the afterlife when the man suddenly toples over in a string of curses. 'JUMP IN' Roman turns around and notices there's a man in a car. Door wide open, A gun in his hand, smoke comming out of it. His whole face is obscured by a mask, only his eyes are visible.

After much delibaration the journalist finaly decided to wear the red suit. After all he hadn't gotten so far in his carrier by blending into the masses and standing out always felt outstanding to him. Adjusting his tie Roman notices the time.
 'SH*T' he swears loudly trying to tie the tie faster but only managing it to tangle it.
 There is no way he's gonna make it on time, unless he's gonna take a shortcut through the notorious Crystal therithory. He's be like a walking target.
 Then again he'd prefer to be punctual to his first important Gala.
 Is his life really worth risking making a good first impression?

Roman decides that being a few minutes late won't make a huge difference and decides to take the longer route. In the end it proves to be a good decision as the party isn't in full swing just yet, when he arrivers.
 Roman breaths out a sign of relief and focus on what he was supposed to do at the party, which is securing an interview with...

Roman figured taking the shortcut was just one more of a risk in his path to greatness. In the end it proved to be a good decision as he arrived safe and sound. He was even a few minutes early. The ballroom is mostly empty so you decide to help yourself to some fingerfood before doing what you were tasked with, which is securing an interview with

Roman spots the famous polititian sorouned by a swarm of woman from all ages. After all this man became so popular due to his his support for women rights and activly fighting for the ban of alcohol. He was getting a lot of side glances. Roman decided to approach him

Roman jumps into the strangers car. If he wanted to shoot him he would have done so while his back was turned to him, Roman reason. Just as the journalist is about to thank the driver the man speaks up.
 'You gotta watch your back Rem. Pat will have your head if I'll have to drag your wounded body to his clinic again.'

The mans eyes widen and he takes a closer look at Roman.
 'Oh crap! You're not Remus!' He says before he takes a sharp U turn rushing back.
 A figure in green jumps onto the road and the driver stops just a few centemeters short of hitting him. As soon as they stop the figure rips the passenger seat open.
 Their eyes widden momentarily before they squeez themselves next to Roman. The driver starts the car before the door fully closses. The sounds of bullets chaisng them.

The man gives him a strange look.
 'Did you hit your head or something?' He reaches out his hand for Romans forehead and Roman bats it away.
 'Hey I'm greatfull and all but I think you've got me mixed up with somebody'

'If you wanted to ditch me you should have done so for someone more handsome then me, Vee.' The man in green states. Is this guy insane? The driver-Vee laughs at the statement. 'You're not setting the bar very hight'
 'You wound me, deer friend' The man gasps dramatically and slides slightly down the seat, earning himself a chuckle from Vee, who turn to Roman. 'Sorry for accidentally kindnapping you.' He says more amused then concerned. 'Where should we drop you off?'

The silence that follows is enough of a sign that Roman should not be asking the question.
 'Think of us as chofeurs for the night' Roman decides it's wise not to press the matter.
 'To the gala then if you don't mind mr. V' Remus snickers at the nickname. They drop him off a block away from the party. Normally Roman would argue but Vee just saved his life and shot a man in front of him so he decided not to press his luck. He walks the few meters.
 The journalist arrivea a few minutes late but the party isn't in full swing just yet.
 Roman breaths out a sign of relief and focus on what he was supposed to do at the party, which is securing an interview with...

Dr.Picani is a man of many trades. Career-wise he is a phycologist but due to his friendly personality and outgoing demeenor he has soon become a public figure. He has led many charities and the town people adore him.
 Popularity runs in the Picani family as his child, Elliot, manages one of the most, if not the most, popular newspapers in the city- The Cartoonist. Roman would kill to be employed by them to prove his worth as a journalist.
 Dr. Picani has stayed away from politics up until this year when he decided to run for the Major office. He is the only candidat that poses a threat to the re-election of Janus.

Dr. Picani stands together with the famous marine admiral and a few other gentle-man. Roman decides to approach them.
 They did not call Roman prince charming in school for nothing as he flawlessly joins the conversation and slowly brings the atention to himself. Picani offers him a trial period at The Cartoonist.
Well i do have a stable job- the future of Romans newspaper hangs on his shoulders.

Roman secures an interview not only with Picani but also with the General.
 Picani get's elected as major and with sweat and tears of Roman and his collegues their newspaper becomes recognisable all over the state
This is the oportunity Roman has been hoping for and he accepts it in a heartbeat.

Virgil sits next to Roman and holds out his hand.
'Come on.I'll hold it until the drug kicks in.'
 'You'll gonna need to remove your shirt before you'll start holding hands with my son.' Virgil snorts at the commen.
 'My shirt?' Roman asks, his words slighty slurred together.
 'Oh now you started being decent?' Virgil jabs at him and Roman has no idea what he's talking about. It's getting harder to focus. 'Did you forget your late night escapade in your birth suit last week? Or was the amount of liquir enough to erase the memory from that empty head of yours.' Roman wanted to say that he has absolutly nothing in common with somebody so uncivilized but he woke up to an empty room instead.

'I'm not getting into your car!'
 The man looks taken aback for a moment before he scrunches up his nose. 'We don't have time for this Prince!'
 He doesn't get the chance to ask why he knows his surname when he hears a grunt behind him. The man came back to his sences and is holding the gun back up and aim at Virgil

Every fiber of Roman's being screams at him to run as fast as he can. His back is turned turned the the man before he can fire the gun. He almost makes it around the corner when he feels a sharp pain in his leg. Before he is able to scream he feels a sharp pain in his head and everything slowly gets black.

Maybe it was his inner heroism or maybe it was just a desperate act of survival but Roman lunges at the man, detecting the bullet as they both fall to the ground. He hears two loud bangs before he's able to rip the gun out of the mans hand. You notice the man from the car above you, the man laying liply on the ground.
 'Come on.' The driver says. 'He's knocked out, let's got.' He says grabbing Roman by the colar and hoisting him in one swift movement to his feet. He starts dragging the journalist to the car with more force then Roman expected.

'Where do you think you're talking me! I have a gala to attend!'
 'Not filled with led, you're not'
 Roman glances at his torso, two wet spots barerly visible in the dim street light. He puts his hand to it, it comes back sticky and warm.
 Roman can fell his feet becoming fuzzy but the driver steadies him.
 'Oh no you're not' He says. 'You're not passing out on me until we make it to your favourite doctor.' He finishes as he pushes Roman onto the passanger seat, runs around the car and starts it as soon as he sits himself on the drivers seat.

You arrive otside of town. As soon as the man stops the car a man opens the door of the building. 'Virgil? What happened?'
'Remus got shot' The driver says as he steps out of the car.
 'I told you not to hang out with them!'
 'You can scold me all you want after we save him. Please?' The mam signs and makes his way to the car. The driver-Virgil turn to Roman once again. His face now filled with concern. 'Can you stand?'
 Roman nopds but as sonn as he tries to a sharp pain shoots through his side. Virgil wordlessly scoops him up. Roman did not expect somebody so lanky to have this much strength.

text:
'Remus. I swear to god I will drop you!' But his smirk betrays him.
 Virgil carries him all the way into the house. The other man following worriedly behind. He brinks him into a room filled with little bottles nad medical equipment to the brim. Virgil lets him down getly onto the operating table and the other man raises a syringe. Roman immediatly shrieks away.
'Whats that? Get that away from me!' He protest. Are they trying to kill him?
'Oh no.'Virgil turns to him, hands on his hips. Last time you insisted on staying awake you trashed the half place when Dad was trying to sew your wounds. You're staying down this time.'
 'If you think I will let myself be drugged, you have another thing comming up sunshine...'
 'Done' Roman looks at the other man. The syringe in his hand is empty. He turns back to Virgil, who's smirking.
 Can't believe it's still this easy to distract you.
 Roman prepares to rebutt him but Virgil takes off his mask and smiles and it takes Roman aback how young he looks. He was expoecting a man in his 40, but Virgil barerly looks 20.

Roman gazes down, his torso is neatly bandaged and he can feel a dull pain coming from his right side. He grimaces when he thinks about the fact thathe most likely just earned himself two scars.
 Roman glances around the room. He sees a little note next to the bed. He picks it up. The whole page is coverd with the word rest in bold letters. Next to it is, what Roman assumes to be, a frowning face. He snorts putting the note down. What a curious pair the doctor and his son are.

Roman stands up, his side throbbing as he does so. He debates whether he should  put on a shirt but he can't find one and his whole torso is covered bin bandages anyway so he gives up on the idea pretty quickly.
 He opens the door as quietly as possible and creeps thoward the sound of voices.
'I'm not looking forward to Dee's scolding...'
 'Well at least Remus safe'
'Yeah. but who is this guy?'
'Do yo think it could be...' Virgil shakes his head.
 'No that's impossible.'
 Whatever they are talking about Roman gets the feeling it isn't meant for his ears.

'You're not ganna, ya know?'Virgil shakes his head.
 'The guy saved me. I doubt he wants me dead.' Virgil lets out a pleasant laugh.'No wonder he argued over getting into the car. He's probably more confused then anything else.' The man lets out a sign. 'You're to good of a person.'
 'I think that stopped being true a long time ago, dad' the man just smiles and shakes his head.
'I just wish...'
 'I know dad.' The silence that fills is awkward and Roman decides he should back out. Just in time as not a second after he settles into bed he hears Virgil knocking on the door.
Roman settles in. He wonders what's beimg said but he doesnt have to wait too long for Virgil to show up, who announces himself with a knock.

'Hey!'Virgil says as he enters the room. There is a plate in his hands, a small cloud of steam rises over it and Roman can smell oatmeal. Virgil looks more interested in the content of the plate then anything else in the room. Roman tries to catch his gaze but to no avail, Virgil keeps standing stifly in the doorway. 'You're...you're ok?'

Virgil snorts and his posture relaxes slightly. He leans against the doorframe, still not meeting Roman's eyes.
 'Sorry for accidentaly kidnapping you.' It's Roman's turn to snort.
'Believe me when I say this is one of the most pleasant kidnappings I've heard of.' Virgil lips tug slightly upwards.

'Hey... um... I should probably give you a ride home.' Virgil finaly utters out. 
'SHIT' Roman tries to shoot up and winces when a sharp pain shoots through his side. Virgil is at his side in a second.
 'You'll ruin the stitches'
 'I'm gonna ruin my reputation if miss the party!' Roman says slightly agitated, which earns him a laugh from Virgil.
 'That's what you're worried about?'
'I was supposed to secure an interview!'
 'You'll be securing some rest after I get you home. You're in no condition to be dancing!' He says gently pushing Roman back onto the operation table. 'Besides. You've slept for a few hours it's almost past 9 in the morning.'
 Roman sinks down dejected.
'I could say the same to you.' He relaxes slightly and leans againt the doorframe.

Virgil gets Roman home. The ride is mostly silent and Virgil shifts a lot but Roman's thoughts are elsewhere. The gala was a big opportunity and he completly blew it. He's not sure he';s rteady to face his boss again on Monday.
